The Truce License
Version 1.0

This is the license for truce. It is a permissive license (MIT or
Apache-2.0, your choice) with one narrow restriction that applies only
if you redistribute truce itself as a commercial framework, or run it
as a commercial service, for other developers. That restriction is the
"Truce Framework Rider" in Section 2.


PLAIN-LANGUAGE SUMMARY (informative; the numbered terms below control)

  If you are building audio plug-ins, plug-in suites, or an internal
  SDK with truce, this license is effectively just MIT / Apache-2.0.
  Build it, ship it, sell it - no permission, no fee, no splash screen,
  no revenue cap, no strings. Most users never need to read past this
  summary.

  The single restriction: you need written permission to take truce
  itself and offer it to other developers as a commercial framework,
  or to run truce as a commercial hosted service that provides its
  framework capabilities to other developers. Free and open-source
  frameworks are exempt. See Section 2.


